#: ../../best_practices/templates.rst:10
msgid "Use Twig templating format for your templates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../best_practices/templates.rst:12
msgid ""
"Generally speaking, PHP templates are much more verbose than Twig templates "
"because they lack native support for lots of modern features needed by "
"templates, like inheritance, automatic escaping and named arguments for "
"filters and functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../best_practices/templates.rst:17
msgid ""
"Twig is the default templating format in Symfony and has the largest "
"community support of all non-PHP template engines (it's used in high profile"
" projects such as Drupal 8)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../best_practices/templates.rst:21
msgid ""
"In addition, Twig is the only template format with guaranteed support in "
"Symfony 3.0. As a matter of fact, PHP may be removed from the officially "
"supported template engines."
msgstr ""

